-- South Africa to Use World Cup Ground in Durban For Record Cricket Crowd
-- Ron Derby
-- 2010-07-15T10:32:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-15/south-africa-to-use-world-cup-ground-in-durban-for-record-cricket-crowd.html

          
          
             Cricket South Africa expects to
attract the biggest-ever crowd at a cricket match in the country
by hosting a 20-20 match between India and South Africa at a
stadium in the city of Durban built for the soccer World Cup.  
 The match will take place on Jan. 9, Michael Owen-Smith, a
spokesman for Cricket South Africa, said in an interview from
his mobile phone today.  
 Durbanâ€™s Moses Mabhida stadium has the capacity to seat
more than 60,000 people while the highest capacity at existing
cricket grounds in South Africa is 30,000, he said.  
